<li id="cite_note-Yc-10"><b><a href="#cite_ref-Yc_10-0" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="web" id="CITEREFP._Gibbs1997">P. Gibbs (1997). <a href="http://math.ucr.edu/home/baez/physics/Relativity/SpeedOfLight/c.html" class="external text" title="http://math.ucr.edu/home/baez/physics/Relativity/SpeedOfLight/c.html" rel="nofollow">"Why is c the symbol for the speed of light?"</a>. <a href="/wiki/University_of_California,_Riverside" title="University of California, Riverside">University of California, Riverside</a><span class="printonly">. <a href="http://math.ucr.edu/home/baez/physics/Relativity/SpeedOfLight/c.html" class="external free" title="http://math.ucr.edu/home/baez/physics/Relativity/SpeedOfLight/c.html" rel="nofollow">http://math.ucr.edu/home/baez/physics/Relativity/SpeedOfLight/c.html</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved on 2008-08-20</span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=Why+is+c+the+symbol+for+the+speed+of+light%3F&amp;rft.atitle=&amp;rft.aulast=P.+Gibbs&amp;rft.au=P.+Gibbs&amp;rft.date=1997&amp;rft.pub=%5B%5BUniversity+of+California%2C+Riverside%5D%5D&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fmath.ucr.edu%2Fhome%2Fbaez%2Fphysics%2FRelativity%2FSpeedOfLight%2Fc.html&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Speed_of_light"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-handbook-11"><b><a href="#cite_ref-handbook_11-0" title="">^</a></b> See, for example, some handbooks:
