<li id="cite_note-Delphenich-33">^ <a href="#cite_ref-Delphenich_33-0" title=""><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Delphenich_33-1" title=""><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="" id="CITEREFD._H._Delphenich2006">D. H. Delphenich (2006). "<a href="http://arxiv.org/abs/hep-th/0610088v1" class="external text" title="http://arxiv.org/abs/hep-th/0610088v1" rel="nofollow">Nonlinear optical analogies in quantum electrodynamics</a>". <i>ArXiv preprint</i><span class="printonly">. <a href="http://arxiv.org/abs/hep-th/0610088v1" class="external free" title="http://arxiv.org/abs/hep-th/0610088v1" rel="nofollow">http://arxiv.org/abs/hep-th/0610088v1</a></span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.atitle=Nonlinear+optical+analogies+in+quantum+electrodynamics&amp;rft.jtitle=ArXiv+preprint&amp;rft.aulast=D.+H.+Delphenich&amp;rft.au=D.+H.+Delphenich&amp;rft.date=2006&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Farxiv.org%2Fabs%2Fhep-th%2F0610088v1&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Speed_of_light"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-Tu-34"><b><a href="#cite_ref-Tu_34-0" title="">^</a></b> This limit established by dispersion in the ionosphere is less restrictive than many others. For a table of limits and their sources see Table I in <cite style="font-style:normal" class="" id="CITEREFAlfred_Scharff_Goldhaber.2C_Michael_Martin_Nieto2008">Alfred Scharff Goldhaber, Michael Martin Nieto (2008). "<a href="http://arxiv.org/abs/0809.1003v2" class="external text" title="http://arxiv.org/abs/0809.1003v2" rel="nofollow">Photon and Graviton Mass Limits</a>". <i>arXiv preprint</i><span class="printonly">. <a href="http://arxiv.org/abs/0809.1003v2" class="external free" title="http://arxiv.org/abs/0809.1003v2" rel="nofollow">http://arxiv.org/abs/0809.1003v2</a></span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.atitle=Photon+and+Graviton+Mass+Limits&amp;rft.jtitle=arXiv+preprint&amp;rft.aulast=Alfred+Scharff+Goldhaber%2C+Michael+Martin+Nieto&amp;rft.au=Alfred+Scharff+Goldhaber%2C+Michael+Martin+Nieto&amp;rft.date=2008&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Farxiv.org%2Fabs%2F0809.1003v2&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Speed_of_light"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span>. For a theoretical presentation, see <cite style="font-style:normal" class="" id="CITEREFLian-Cheng_Tu_.27.27et_al..27.272005">Lian-Cheng Tu <i>et al.</i> (2005). "<a href="http://ggg.hust.edu.cn/publication/2005/1%20RPP%20The%20mass%20of%20the%20photon.pdf" class="external text" title="http://ggg.hust.edu.cn/publication/2005/1%20RPP%20The%20mass%20of%20the%20photon.pdf" rel="nofollow">The mass of the photon</a>". <i>Rep Prog Phys</i> <b>68</b>: 77-130. <a href="/wiki/Digital_object_identifier" title="Digital object identifier">doi</a>:<span class="neverexpand"><a href="http://dx.doi.org/10.1088%2F0034-4885%2F68%2F1%2FR02" class="external text" title="http://dx.doi.org/10.1088%2F0034-4885%2F68%2F1%2FR02" rel="nofollow">10.1088/